attributes.Long form description: The student is to disassemble the rolling cart. The student turns over the rolling cart and starts to disassemble the four wheels. Then the student unscrews the hexagon cap nuts and the screws. Next, the student removes the brackets and the trays. Then the student disassembles the bars and the base frame. Lastly, the student puts them together on the table neatly.

attributes.Transcription: We will now disassemble the rolling shelf from IKEA, RASHULT.
So please go ahead and disassemble.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles all four wheels from the furniture.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student drops the recently unscrewed wheel by accident.

attributes.Action sentence: The student detaches the brackets from the middle and top tray.
The student disassembles all three trays.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: Student drops the nut by accident.
Student should not drop the bracket.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles all the legs.
